@page "/"

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1>Welcome to Data Patrol</h1>

    <p class="lead">
        This application is the technical assignment deliverable for DataPatrol’s Full‑Stack Developer role.
        It demonstrates a complete end‑to‑end solution built with modern ASP.NET Core and Blazor.
    </p>

    <h5>Key Features:</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Data Model &amp; Multi‑Tenancy Ready</strong><br />
            EF Core entities for Users, Groups, Policies, Requests, with many‑to‑many mappings and cascade rules.
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>Repository &amp; Unit‑of‑Work Pattern</strong><br />
            Clean data‑access abstraction (IGenericRepository, UnitOfWork) for OOP, testability, and SRP.
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>Design Patterns &amp; OOP</strong><br />
            Generic repositories, DI, DTO mapping, and inheritance used throughout for maintainability.
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>Memory Management</strong><br />
            <ul>
                <li>DbContext scoped and disposed automatically by DI container.</li>
                <li>.AsNoTracking() on all read‑only queries to avoid change‑tracker bloat.</li>
                <li>Optional DbContext pooling enabled to reduce allocations under load.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>Blazor Server UI</strong><br />
            MudBlazor+Bootstrap for responsive pages, modals, and client‑side routing.
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>RESTful API Endpoints</strong><br />
            • POST /api/User/reg for registration<br />
            • POST /api/Request/create and POST /api/Request/summary<br />
            • Full CRUD on Users, Groups, Policies, Requests<br />
            • GET /api/Random 
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
            <strong>Background Worker</strong><br />
            Processes pending requests every 10 seconds, updating status with error handling.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <p>
        Use the navigation menu to explore and manage each section.
        Feel free to drill into Users, User Groups, Policies, or User Requests to see full create/edit/delete flows.
    </p>
</div>